BeanBoozled with the boys
VSS 8lbs 8oz 6:31 pm 1/16/23
And I don’t wanna bore you with it, but oh I love you, I love you, I love you ❤️

Instagram used to be a place where I’d show you guys my workouts, meals, vacations etc. Today, I look at this app totally differently. I look at it as a photo album one day my kids can access and look back on their lives. I’ve got some photos of my mom. Not a whole lot. Not many videos where I can watch and hear her speak. I wish I did! So if one day I’m gone and you’re reading this Axel, Ozzy & Van, dad loves you to infinity and beyond!

Watching Paw Patrol probably or some other kids show I’m not interested in. Spit up on my chest. These moments I typically am like ugh let me up. Let me go do something I want to do like workout or go watch a show or podcast I’m interested or just shower. But then I remind myself, if this life were to come to an end and I was given the opportunity to go back to any moment in time, it’d be these. Funny how that works. The moments that are probably the most special are the boring uninteresting ones we often take most for granted.
